core.name: CoreInterrupt
core.description:
The CoreInterrupt module is an APB slave that provides configurable interrupt processing.
CoreInterrupt supports 0 to 32 IRQ interrupt sources and 0 to 8 FIQ sources. The IRQ and FIQ interrupt source inputs are level sensitive, active high ports. These interrupt sources are processed to produce two output interrupt lines, IRQ and FIQ. All interrupt processing is combinational; that is, the paths from the IRQ/FIQ source inputs to the IRQ/FIQ output contain no flip-flops.
Software driven IRQ/FIQ interrupts are supported and each IRQ/FIQ source can be individually enabled or disabled via control registers.

core.name: CoreRemap
core.description: CoreRemap is an APB slave which provides a system control register which can be used to alter the system memory map. The Remap output from CoreRemap can be connected to the Remap input of CoreAHB or CoreAHBLite where it is used to swap AHB slave slots 0 and 1 when asserted.

core.name: CoreWatchdog
core.description: The CoreWatchdog unit is an APB slave that provides a means of recovering from software crashes. When enabled, CoreWatchdog will generate a soft reset for the system if the microprocessor fails to refresh it on a regular basis.

core.name: COREDES
core.description: The CoreDES macro implements the Data Encryption Standard (DES), which provides a means of securing data. The DES algorithm is described in Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) Publication (PUB) 46-3.

core_mlv.name: LVDS_TX_7_1

core_mlv.name: CORERISCV_AXI4
core_mlv.description: CoreRISC-V_AXI4 is based on SiFive's E31 Coreplex advanced RISC-V core built by SiFive, Inc. CoreRISC-V_AXI4 supports the RV32IM architecture, with a 32-bit datapath and implementing the I(Base Integer) and M (Integer Multiply and Divide) extensions. This CoreRISC-V_AXI4 also contains: - 8kB instruction cache, - 8kB data cache, - PLIC (programmable interrupt controller), - JTAG debug interface. The coreplex interfaces with the external system via two AXI4 compliant master buses, one for memory accesses and one for memory-mapped I/O accesses.

core_mlv.name: CoreTimer
core_mlv.description:
The CoreTimer module is an APB slave that provides access to an interrupt-generating, programmable decrementing counter.
The width of the decrementing counter in the CoreTimer module can be statically configured as either 16 or 32 bits. Programmable registers provide a means to dynamically control the operation of the timer.
Two modes of operation are available for CoreTimer: Continuous mode and One-shot timer mode.

core_mlv.description: -Computes Natural Logarithm of an unsigned number -Computes Square root of an unsigned number

core_mlv.name: COREQEI
core_mlv.description: The CoreQEI component decodes speed and motion sensor information. It can be used in any application that uses a quadrature encoder for feedback.

core_mlv.name: CORESDR_AXI
core_mlv.description: CoreSDR_AXI provides a high-performace interface to single-data-rate (SDR) synchronous dynamic random access memory (SDRAM) devices via an AMBA eXtensible Interface.

core_mlv.name: COREMACFILTER

core_mlv.name: COREMDIO_APB
core_mlv.description: The CoreMDIO_APB has the following features: IEEE 802.3 Clause 22 standard MDIO interface APB Slave interface for register access Busy status information for user application MDC prescale

core_mlv.name: CORERESET_PF
core_mlv.description: CoreReset_PF will allow synchronization of the resets to the user-specified clock domain into which each reset is feeding, so that while assertion is asynchronous, negation is synchronous to the clock.

core_mlv.name: COREAHBLTOAXI
core_mlv.description: The CoreAHBLtoAXI is an AHBLite slave and an AXI master that provides an interface (bridge) between the AHB domain and AXI domain. The CoreAHBLtoAXI allows an AHBLite bus system to be connected to an AXI bus. The AHBLite to AXI Bridge enables the AHBLite master to communicate with AXI slave. It allows the AHBL bus to initiate data transfer between the two buses. The AHBL slave interface and AXI master interface allows the AHBL bus and AXI bus to access the read/write buffer memor

core_mlv.name: CoreConfigMaster
core_mlv.description: Masters peripheral configuration in a SmartFusion2 or IGLOO2 device.

core_mlv.name: COREHPDMACTRL
core_mlv.description: The CoreHPDMACtrl Soft IP is used to control the HPDMA of the HPMS/MSS and also monitors the transaction status. The HPDMA buffer descriptors are initialized through the core configuration. The CoreHPDMACtrl selects the buffer descriptor and initiates the transactions. It also monitors the interrupts for transfer done and error. The Soft IP also re-programs the registers to prepare the HPDMA of the HPMS/MSS for next transfer.

core_mlv.name: CORERGMII
core_mlv.description: Converts GMII to RGMII

core_mlv.name: COREMBX
core_mlv.description: CoreMBX (Mail Box) allows data messages (mail) to pass back and forth from one processing element to another. The user is able to choose (via CoreConsole or SmartDesign configuration) whether this message passing capability is implemented with one or more instances of dual-port SRAM hard macros or with one or more instances of FIFO hard macros.

core_mlv.name: CoreAXI4Interconnect
core_mlv.description: The AMBA AXI4 Interconnect core connects one or more AXI memory-mapped master devices to one or more memory-mapped slave devices. The AMBA AXI protocol supports high-performance, high-frequency system designs.

core_mlv.name: COREAHBLSRAM
core_mlv.description: The CoreAHBLSRAM provides access to the embedded large SRAM blocks present on SmartFusion2 family devices through AHB-Lite slave interface. It will facilitate convenient access to SRAM by AHB masters. Read and write transactions on the AHB are converted into corresponding transfers on the LSRAM or uSRAM.

core_mlv.name: CORETBITOEPCS
core_mlv.description: The bridge appears between the Ten-Bit Interface (TBI) and External PCS (EPCS). The Core supports Ten-Bit interface Rx/Tx data bus on TBI side and 20-bit Rx/Tx data bus on EPCS side. This block receive TBI data (with double data rate) and transmit on EPCS bus and vice-versa. CoreTBItoEPCS includes user testbench for verification.

core_mlv.name: CoreSF2Config
core_mlv.description: Facilitiates configuration of peripheral blocks (MDDR, FDDR and SERDESIF) in a SmartFusion2 device.

core_mlv.name: COREAPBLSRAM
core_mlv.description: The CoreAPBLSRAM provides access to the embedded large SRAM blocks present on SmartFusion2 family devices through APB slave interface. It will facilitate convenient access to Fabric SRAM by APB masters. Read and write transactions on the APB are converted into corresponding transfers on the LSRAM and uSRAM.

core_mlv.name: CORESDLC
core_mlv.description: The CoreSDLC macro provides a high-speed synchronous serial communication controller that utilizes the Synchronous Data Link Control (SDLC) protocol. Operation of the controller is similar to that used in the Intel 8XC152 Global Serial Channel (GSC) device working in SDLC mode under CPU control. Communication with a CPU is realized through the Advanced Peripheral Bus (APB) interface and three interrupt sources. This enables CoreSDLC to be easily interfaced with any CPU.

core_mlv.name: CORETSE
core_mlv.description: - Tri-Speed Ethernet MAC core - Full duplex support at 10/100/1000 Mbps - Half duplex support at 10/100 Mbps - TBI interface for 1000Base-T and 1000Base-X - MDIO management interface for PHY register access - Advanced peripheral bus (APB) control interface - Wake-On-LAN detection - Frame Statistics Counters - Destination Address Based Frame Filtering

core_mlv.name: CORETSE_AHB
core_mlv.description: Tri-Speed Ethernet MAC core with following features: - Tri-Speed Ethernet MAC Core - 10/100/1000 Mbps Operation - Full-Duplex at 10/100/1000 Mbps - Half-Duplex at 10/100 Mbps - Standard G/MII interface - MDIO interface for PHY register access -Ten-bit interface (TBI) for 1000Base-T or 1000Base-X support - Wake on LAN (WoL) with Magic Packet Detection - Frame Statistics Counters - Destination Address Based Filtering

core_mlv.name: COREAXI
core_mlv.description: The CoreAXI v3.0 is multi-master multiple-slave AXI3 bus interconnect. It provides 4 AXI MASTER interfaces and up to 16 AXI SLAVE interfaces. The number of AXI masters and slaves to be connected is programmable through parameter configuration. The IP core also provides feedthrough mode for single slave and single master configuration only.

core_mlv.name: CoreGPIO
core_mlv.description: CoreGPIO provides APB access to 32 general purpose IOs, with configurable per bit enabling and interrupt generation.

core_mlv.name: CORESYSSERVICES
core_mlv.description: The system services are system controller actions initiated by asynchronous events from the master in the FPGA fabric or external User Interface corresponding to each service. CoreSysServices soft IP provides access to the system services. The CoreSysServices soft IP communicates with the COMM_BLK through one of the FIC interfaces. The CoreSysServices handles the system services grouped together into following groups of services: Device and Design Information Services Flash*Freeze Service Programming Service Cryptographic Services PUF Services DPA-Resistant Key-Tree Services Non-Deterministic Random Bit Generator (NRBG) Services Zeroization Service Digest Check Service Unrecognized Command Response

core_mlv.name: CORELPC
core_mlv.description: CoreLPC is a low pin count (LPC) peripheral APB component which accepts LPC host-side system interface commands to the APB-slave side keyboard control style (KCS) interface. Alternatively, LPC traffic can be sent directly to/from other APB peripherals via an APB Master Interface. Serial interrupt request (SERIRQ) logic may be utilized to aggregate interrupts onto a single line.

core_mlv.name: CORE16550
core_mlv.description: The Core16550 is a standard UART providing 100% software compatibility with the popular Texas Instruments 16550 device. It performs serial-to-parallel conversion on data originating from modems or other serial devices, and performs parallel-to-serial conversion on data from a CPU to these devices. When transmitting, the data is written into the transmit FIFO of the UART. The data is then transmitted in serial form. When receiving data, the UART transforms the serial input data into a parallel form to facilitate reading by the processor. Build time: 2012-05-11-12:10 GMT

core_mlv.name: CorePCS
core_mlv.description: The CorePCS supports programmable 8B10B encoding/decoding. 8B10B is commonly used in protocols not supported by the SmartFusion2 SERDES Interface so this core would be ideal for the end user that wants to make use of this core with other protocols. The core can be configured as a transmitter only, receiver only or both transmitter and receiver. Word alignment support is included in the receiver. The core can be configured to support 10bit or 20bit EPCS data.

core_mlv.name: STEPPER_THETA

core_mlv.name: SVM

core_mlv.name: ENCODER_INTERFACE

core_mlv.name: FOC_TRANSFORMS

core_mlv.name: OLMNG
core_mlv.description: Open Loop Manager - Generates open loop angle - Multiplexes open loop angle and closed loop angle based on closed loop status - Provides init values for PI controllers

core_mlv.name: SEQ_CONTROLLER
core_mlv.description: Sequence Controller - Implements a top level motor controller FSM.

core_mlv.name: PWM3PH
core_mlv.description: Three Phase PWM generation with configurable dead time and delay time.

core_mlv.name: ADC_SCALING
core_mlv.description: Provides the following functionality - 1. Auto calibrates ADC channel offsets. 2. Scaling of ADC data 3. Provides overcurrent fault information. 4. Configurable for signed or unsigned data

core_mlv.name: BLDC_ESTIMATOR
core_mlv.description: BLDC Position Speed Estimator

core_mlv.name: CORE1553BRT
core_mlv.description: RELEASE VERSION - MIL-STD-1553B is a 1 Mb/s command/response, dual-redundant, time-multiplexed serial data bus used in aircraft, spacecraft, military vehicles, and severe control environments. Core1553BRT provides a complete, MIL-STD-1553B Remote Terminal (RT), and is compatible with legacy remote terminal systems and supports standard off-chip 1553B transceivers.

core_mlv.name: COREPWM
core_mlv.description: CorePWM is a general purpose multi channel Pulse Width Modulator (PWM) module for Motor Control, Tone Generation, Battery Charging, Heating Elements, etc. In addition, there is a special 'Low Ripple DAC' mode that creates a pulse train that does not modulate the width of the pulses. Instead, the algorithm for generating the pulses is such that when used with a low pass filter (such as a simple RC circuit), a DAC can be created with far better bandwidth and ripple performance than could be achieved with a standard PWM algorithm. This type of DAC is ideally suited for fine tuning of power supply output levels.

core_mlv.name: CORE10100
core_mlv.description: CORE10100 is an Ethernet Media Access Controller that connects Local Area Networks at data rates of 10 or 100 Mb/s. It supports either a Media Independent Interface (MII) or Reduced Media Independent Interface (RMII) for physical connection and implements Carrier Sense Multiple Access with Collision Detection (CSMA/CD) algorithms per IEEE 802.3

core_mlv.name: CORE10100_AHBAPB
core_mlv.description: CORE10100_AHBAPB is an Ethernet Media Access Controller with a APB control and AHB data interface that connects Local Area Networks at data rates of 10 or 100 Mb/s. It supports either a Media Independent Interface (MII) or Reduced Media Independent Interface (RMII) for physical connection and implements Carrier Sense Multiple Access with Collision Detection (CSMA/CD) algorithms per IEEE 802.3

core_mlv.name: CORESPI
core_mlv.description: CoreSPI is a controller core designed for synchronous serial communication using the Motorola, TI, or NSC Serial Peripheral Interface (SPI). The core is parameterized to allow user specification of clock phase, clock polarity, slave select behavior, FIFO depth, frame width, and mode. Operation is fully synchronous and operates on the system clock as well as the external SPI clock for slave mode.

core_mlv.name: CoreConfigP
core_mlv.description: Facilitiates configuration of peripheral blocks (MDDR, FDDR and SERDESIF) in a SmartFusion2 or IGLOO2 device.

core_mlv.name: CoreResetP
core_mlv.description: Facilitiates sequencing of reset signals in a SmartFusion2 device.

core_mlv.name: COREI2C
core_mlv.description: CoreI2C provides an APB-driven serial interface, supporting I2C, SMBus, PMBus, and IPMI data transfers. Verilog/VHDL parameters are available to configure operation modes and minimize FPGA fabric area for a given application. CoreI2C allows for the generation of up to 16 I2C Channels per APB slot.

core_mlv.name: COREBOOTSTRAP
core_mlv.description: CoreBootStrap facilitates booting a soft processor from a SPI flash device indirectly by first copying boot code from SPI to this RAM, then allowing the processor to boot from there.

core_mlv.name: COREQDR

core_mlv.name: COREAXI4DMACONTROLLER
core_mlv.description: CoreAXI4DMAController is an AXI4 DMA controller designed to perform memory to memory style DMA (Direct Memory Access) transfers in an AXI system. In addition the core provides a bridge to AXI4 memory-mapped slaves for AXI4-Stream masters.

core_mlv.name: CoreMemCtrl
core_mlv.description: The Memory Controller is an AHB slave component which supports access to external SRAM and Flash memory resources. The core uses 1 slave slot on the AHB bus.

core_mlv.name: COREFIFO
core_mlv.description: CoreFIFO is a fully configurable Soft FIFO controller. It is designed to support SmartFusion2, IGLOO2, RTG4, PolarFire and PolarFireSoC device family.

core_mlv.name: COREPCIE_AXITOAHBL
core_mlv.description: The CorePCIe_AXItoAHBL is an AXI slave and an AHBL master that provides an interface (bridge) between the AXI domain and AHB domain. The CorePCIe_AXItoAHBL allows an AXI bus system to be connected to an AHB bus system. The AXI to AHB Bridge enables the AXI master to communicate with AHB slave. It allows the AXI bus to initiate data transfer between the two buses.

core_mlv.name: COREPCIE_AHBLTOAXI
core_mlv.description: The CorePCIe_AHBLtoAXI is an AHBLite slave and an AXI master that provides an interface (bridge) between the AHB domain and AXI domain. The CorePCIe_AHBLtoAXI allows an AHBLite bus system to be connected to an AXI bus. The AHBLite to AXI Bridge enables the AHBLite master to communicate with AXI slave. It allows the AHBL bus to initiate data transfer between the two buses. The AHBL slave interface and AXI master interface allows the AHBL bus and AXI bus to access the read or write buffer memory

core_mlv.name: Alpha_Blending
core_mlv.description: Alpha Blending is a per pixel mixture of two video streams.Supporting pixel width of 8,10,12,14,16. Supports AXI4 Video Stream and AXI4 Lite Config. Interface.

core_mlv.name: Bayer_Interpolation
core_mlv.description: Converts color filter array to RGB using Bilinear Interpolation followed by Freeman Median Filtering. Supports AXI4 Video Stream and AXI4-Lite Config. Interface.

core_mlv.name: RGBtoYCbCr
core_mlv.description: Conversion of RGB to YCbCr space. Supports data wodth of 8,10 &12. Also supports YCbCr444 to YCbCr 422 conversion for 1 pixel. Supports AXI4 Video Stream.

core_mlv.name: YCbCrtoRGB
core_mlv.description: Conversion of YCbCr to RGB space. Supports 8,10 & 12 data width. Also supports YCbCr422 to YCbCr444 conversion for 1 pixel.Supporting AXI4 Video Stream.

core_mlv.name: Gamma_Correction
core_mlv.description: Provides linear luminance or RGB values for non-linear display characteristics. Supports for data width of 8 and 10. Supports AXI4 Stream Video Interface.

core_mlv.name: HDMI_RX
core_mlv.description: HDMI Receiver. Supports AXI4 Stream Video Interface.

core_mlv.name: Edge_Detection
core_mlv.description: Detects the edges in a image using 3x3 Sobel Kernal. Supporting AXI4 Stream Video Interface.

core_mlv.name: CORECIC
core_mlv.description: Cascaded Integrator-Comb multirate filter can be configured to decimate or interpolate input signal. The core supports fixed or programmable rate change from 2 to 1024, one to eight integrator-comb stages. Time shared hardware is used to implement up to 64 data channels at minimal resource utilization. Input and output data widths are configurable as well, as a choice of Hogenauer pruning and output rounding techniques. Differential comb delay values of one and two are implemented

core_mlv.name: CoreJESD204BTX
core_mlv.description: CoreJESD204BTX is the transmitter interface of the JEDEC JESD204B standard. This specification describes a high speed serial interface for data converters

core_mlv.name: CORERSDEC
core_mlv.description: CoreRSDEC is a parameterizable Reed-Solomon Decoder with following features: - Code symbol width from 3 to 8 bits - Codeword length up to 255 symbols - User-defined finite field primitive polynomial - Error correction capacity up to 16 symbols - Shortened code support in conventional decoder mode - Conventional, CCSDS-8, and CCSDS-16 modes - Erasure support in conventional and CCSDS mode

core_mlv.name: Histogram
core_mlv.description: Histogram plotting of real-time video and Curve based correction of live video. Supports AXI4 Stream Video Interface.

core_mlv.name: COREFIR
core_mlv.description: Finite Impulse Response (FIR) filter utilizing hard multiplier-accumulator (MAC) blocks. Choose between single rate Fully Enumerated, single rate Folded and multi-rate Polyphase interpolation or decimation FIR filter implementations. The core supports filters with constant coefficients, constant multiple coefficient sets, or run-time reloadable coefficients. Number of filter taps ranges from 2 to 1024 depending on the filter type, and number of available MAC. The filter accepts signed data and coefficients of up to 18 bits wide, and unsigned data/coefficients of up to 17 bits.

core_mlv.name: CORE1553BRM

core_mlv.name: MIV_RV32IMC
core_mlv.description:
The MIV_RV32IMC is a processor core designed to implement the RISC-V instruction set for use in Microchip FPGAs
It includes the following features: Designed for low power FPGA soft-core implementations Supports the RISC-V standard RV32I ISA with optional Multiply and Divide (M) and Compressed (C) extensions Tightly coupled memory is available and size is defined by address range Direct Access Port (DAP) to TCM External, Timer and Soft Interrupts Up to six optional external interrupts Vectored and non-vectored interrupt support Optional on-chip debug unit with a JTAG interface AHBL, APB3, and AXI3/AXI4 optional external bus interfaces

core_mlv.name: CORESDR
core_mlv.description: CORESDR provides a high performance interface to single data rate(SDR) synchronous dynamic random access memory(SDRAM) devices. CORESDR accepts read and write commands using the simple local bus interface, and translates these requests to the command sequences required by SDRAM devices. CORESDR also performs all initialization and refresh functions. CORESDR uses bank management techniques to monitor the status of each SDRAM bank. Banks are only opened or closed when necessary, minimizing access delays. Up to four banks can be managed at one time.

core_mlv.name: CORECOLDET
core_mlv.description: This IP detects collision when there is simultaneous read/write access to the same location at the same time. The implementation will give priority to write over read.

core_mlv.name: alpha_blending
core_mlv.description: Alpha Blending is a per pixel mixture of two video streams.Supporting pixel width of 8,10,12,14,16.

core_mlv.name: COREUHD_SDIRX
core_mlv.description: CoreUHD_SDIRX is a SDI Deframer. CoreUHD_SDIRX performs the deframing of the SDI data stream into raw video data.

core_mlv.name: COREUHD_SDITX
core_mlv.description: CoreUHD_SDITX is a SDI Framer. CoreUHD_SDITX performs the framing of the raw video data into SDI data stream. Core supports 12G-SDI, 6G-SDI, 3G-SDI and HD-SDI data rates.

core_mlv.name: MIV_RV32
core_mlv.description:
The MIV_RV32 is a processor core designed to implement the RISC-V instruction set for use in Microchip FPGAs
It includes the following features: Designed for low power FPGA soft-core implementations Supports the RISC-V standard RV32I ISA with optional Multiply and Divide (M) and Compressed (C) extensions Tightly coupled memory is available and size, up to 256Kb max, is defined by address range. BOOTROM feature which will copy an image from a source memory location to a destination memory location and then run code from the destination memory TCM APB Slave (TAS) port to TCM External, Timer and Soft Interrupts Up to six optional external interrupts Vectored and non-vectored interrupt support Optional on-chip debug unit with a JTAG interface AHBL, APB3, and AXI3/AXI4 optional external bus interfaces

core_mlv.name: COREEDAC
core_mlv.description: Actel optimized Error Detection And Correction logic protects data stored in a RAM block. It detects double bit errors and corrects any single bit soft (transient) errors in RAM words from 4 to 64 bits wide. The core utilizes a specific shortened Hamming code as well, as optional pipelining to achieve high performance. The EDAC logic optionally implements RAM scrubbing, a procedure that prevents the RAM of accumulating the soft errors.

core_mlv.name: dp_transmitter
core_mlv.description: Display port transmitter.

core_mlv.name: White_Balance
core_mlv.description: Supports data width of 8,10,12 and 16.

core_mlv.name: CORE3DES
core_mlv.description: The Core3DES macro implements the Triple Data Encryption Standard (3DES or Triple DES), which provides a means of securing data. The Triple DES algorithm is described in Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) Publication (PUB) 46-3 and is an extension of the DES (Data Encryption Standard) algorithm.

core_mlv.name: CORE429
core_mlv.description: Core429 provides a complete Transmitter(Tx) and Receiver(Rx). Core429 requires connection to an external CPU. The CPU interface configures the transmit and receive control registers and initializes the label memory. The core interfaces to the ARINC 429 bus through an external ARINC 429 line driver and line receiver. The core include a user testbench for system verification and a comprehensive testbench to verify core performance against the datasheet.

core_mlv.name: CORE429_APB
core_mlv.description: Core429_APB provides a complete Transmitter(Tx) and Receiver(Rx). Core429 requires connection to an external CPU. The CPU interface configures the transmit and receive control registers and initializes the label memory. The core interfaces to the ARINC 429 bus through an external ARINC 429 line driver and line receiver. The core include a user testbench for system verification and a comprehensive testbench to verify core performance against the datasheet.

core_mlv.name: CORE1553BRT_APB
core_mlv.description: MIL-STD-1553B is a 1 Mb/s command/response, dual-redundant, time-multiplexed serial data bus used in aircraft, spacecraft, military vehicles, and severe control environments. Core1553BRT provides a complete, MIL-STD-1553B Remote Terminal (RT), and is compatible with legacy remote terminal systems and supports standard off-chip 1553B transceivers. This version provides a APB interface with internal buffer memory

core_mlv.name: CoreAHBLite
core_mlv.description: The CoreAHBLite component implements a multi-master AHB-Lite bus. It provides up to 4 AHB-Lite master interfaces, and up to 16 AHB-Lite slave interfaces. It is possible to allocate one or more slave slots to a "combined region" that is accessed through a further slave interface. Slave slots allocated to the combined region are not available for separate connection.

core_mlv.name: COREAHBTOAPB3
core_mlv.description: The CoreAHBtoAPB3 is an AHB slave and APB master that bridges between the AHB domain and the APB domain. CoreAHBtoAPB3 can be used to connect between CoreAHB or CoreAHBLite and CoreAPB3.

core_mlv.name: CoreAPB3
core_mlv.description: The CoreAPB3 component implements an APB3 (AMBA3 APB) fabric, which is backwards compatible with APB2 slave peripherals.There is one APB3 Master interface.

core_mlv.name: COREMMC
core_mlv.description: CoreMMC provides an eMMC controller for interfacing to eMMC devices. The core is parameterized to allow user specification of MMC data bus width & FIFO depth and is conformant to the JEDEC eMMC v4.41 Standard Specification. CoreMMC consists of an AMBA High-Performance Bus Lite (AHB-Lite) slave inteface designed to connect to an AHB-Lite bus. Its registers, including write and read data FIFOs can be accessed by an AHBL master.

core_mlv.name: COREPCIF
core_mlv.description: PCI is a complex interface with a wide variety of uses in computer and embedded systems applications. CorePCIF expands on the popular CorePCI by adding a FIFO interface. CorePCIF is the most versatile FPGA PCI core available because it is capable of 33/66 MHz operation with either 32 or 64-bit bus widths in master, target, and master/target configurations. The master configuraation includes a built-in DMA controller. CorePCIF includes a user testbench for system verification and a comprehensive testbench too verify core performance against the datasheet

core_mlv.name: COREPCIF_AHB
core_mlv.description: PCI is a complex interface with a wide variety of uses in computer and embedded systems applications. CorePCIF AHB expands on the popular CorePCIF by adding an AHB slave interface allowing PCI interfaces to be automatically added to systems created in CoreConsole. CorePCIF AHB supports 32-Bit PCI and AHB buses with 33/66 MHz PCI operation in master, target, and master/target configurations. The master configuration includes a built-in DMA controller. CorePCIF AHB includes testbenchs for system verification

core_mlv.name: corepwm
core_mlv.description: CorePWM is a general purpose multi channel Pulse Width Modulator (PWM) module for Motor Control, Tone Generation, Battery Charging, Heating Elements, etc. In addition, there is a special 'Low Ripple DAC' mode that creates a pulse train that does not modulate the width of the pulses. Instead, the algorithm for generating the pulses is such that when used with a low pass filter (such as a simple RC circuit), a DAC can be created with far better bandwidth and ripple performance than could be achieved with a standard PWM algorithm. This type of DAC is ideally suited for fine tuning of power supply output levels.

core_mlv.name: CORERMII
core_mlv.description: Reduced Media Independent Interface (RMII) is a standard which was developed to reduce the number of signals required to connect a PHY to a MAC. CoreRMII provides interconversion between MII and RMII protocol.

core_mlv.name: CORERSENC
core_mlv.description: CoreRSENC (Reed-Solomon Encoder) is a parameterizable encoder to be used in forward error correction applications. The Reed-Solomon Encoder generates (n, k) block codes. The maximum number of correctable errors is (n-k)/2. The encoder supports CCSDS mode

core_mlv.name: CORESGMII
core_mlv.description: The CoreSGMII provides a solution for ten bit interface (TBI) on gigabit media independent interface (G/MII) based designs - Full-duplex support for 1000 Mbps operation - Full and half-duplex support for 10/100 Mbps operation - Internal or external G/MII for interfacing to a MAC - MDIO interface to configure and monitor - Implements 8b/10b encoding and decoding - Clause 37 Auto-Negotiation - Ten Bit Interface - Comma alignment

core_mlv.name: COREUART
core_mlv.description: CoreUART is a serial communication controller with a flexible serial data interface that is intended primarily for embedded systems. The controller operates in an asynchronous (UART) The core includes a user testbench to show sample UART operation.

core_mlv.name: COREQSPI
core_mlv.description: CoreQSPI supports in Master mode as a controller for SPI protocol engine to provide SPI flash data transfers. The AHB slave system interface is used to configure the controller operation in different modes like Full SPI BI/Quad mode and Extended SPI BI/Quad Mode.

core_mlv.name: CNN_ENGINE
core_mlv.description: Hardware acceleration of Convolution Neural Networks. Supports dynamic network change without reprogramming the device.

core_mlv.name: COREAHBL2AHBL_BRIDGE
core_mlv.description: The COREAHBL2AHBL_BRIDGE is used to connect two AHB-Lite buses clocked by asynchronous clocks. This bridge supports Single, INCR4, INCR8, INCR16 burst type.

core_mlv.name: LiteFast
core_mlv.description: Light Weight Serial Protocol for High Speed Applications

core_mlv.name: COREAXITOAHBL
core_mlv.description: The CoreAXItoAHBL is an AXI3/AXI4 slave and an AHBL master that provides an interface (bridge) between the AXI domain and AHB domain. The CoreAXItoAHBL allows an AXI bus system to be connected to an AHB bus system. The AXI to AHB Bridge enables the AXI master to communicate with AHB slave. It allows the AXI bus to initiate data transfer between the two buses.

core_mlv.name: COREJTAGDEBUG
core_mlv.description: CoreJTAGDebug facilitates the connection of JTAG (Joint Test Action Group) compatible soft core processors to the JTAG header for debugging.

core_mlv.name: CoreJESD204BRX
core_mlv.description: CoreJESD204BRX is the receiver interface of the JEDEC JESD204B standard. This specification describes a high speed serial interface for data converters

core_mlv.name: COREAXITOAXICONNECT
core_mlv.description: An AXI to AXI Connector that connects a slave interface of one CoreAXI4Interconnect module with master interface of another CoreAXI4Interconnect module with no intervening logic.

core_mlv.name: CORESDR_AHB
core_mlv.description: CoreSDR_AHB provides a high performance interface to single data rate(SDR) synchronous dynamic random access memory(SDRAM) devices. CoreSDR_AHB accepts read and write commands using the AHB bus slave interface, and translates these requests to the command sequences required by SDRAM devices. CoreSDR_AHB also performs all initialization and refresh functions. CoreSDR_AHB uses bank management techniques to monitor the status of each SDRAM bank. Banks are only opened or closed when necessary, minimizing access delays. Up to four banks can be managed at one time.

core_mlv.name: CORECORDIC
core_mlv.description: Coordinate rotation digital computer supports vector rotation and translation modes to compute sine, cosine and arctan values, perform general vector rotation, convert from polar to rectangular coordinates and vice versa. The core implements configurable data width of 8 to 48 bits as well, as variety of rounding options. Optional coarse rotation can be selected to extend rotation range to a full circle

core_mlv.name: COREDDS
core_mlv.description: Direct digital synthesizer or Numerically controlled oscillator generates parameterizable sine and/or cosine digital sample train. The core supports phase accumulation up to 32 bits and up to 1048576 effective Look-up table depth. The output samples are up to 32-bit wide. The core provides optional inputs for phase and frequency offsets, phase dithering and trigonometric phase correction. The core supports user control over the design latency.

core_mlv.name: COREFFT
core_mlv.description: Depending on user configuration, CoreFFT generates one of the two supported transformation implementations. Streaming FFT: The architecture supports continuous complex data processing, one input data sample per clock period. In-place FFT: The transform loads a frame of N complex data samples in the in-place RAM, and process them sequentially, stage by stage. CoreFFT utilizes hard multiplier-accumulator blocks (MACC) available on RTG4, SmartFusion2, IGLOO2, PolarFire and PolarFireSoC parts. The core implements Forward or Inverse FFT with scaling. Transform sizes supported are: 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024, 2048, 4096, 8192 and 16384 points. The core supports input and output data bit resolution in the range of 8 to 32 bits.
